---
import DocsLayout from '../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<DocsLayout title="Session Management" activeNav="session-management" description="Max concurrent session enforcement, revocation, and background cleanup.">

  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Araxys provides server-side session management with three key capabilities: <strong>concurrent session enforcement</strong>
    (revoke the oldest session when a limit is exceeded), <strong>manual session revocation</strong> for immediate
    invalidation, and a <strong>background cleanup loop</strong> that periodically purges expired sessions. Sessions
    work alongside JWT authentication and CSRF protection for a complete auth pipeline.
  </p>

  <h2 id="how-it-works">How It Works</h2>

  <h3 id="concurrent-enforcement">Concurrent Session Enforcement</h3>
  <p>
    When a user exceeds <code>max_concurrent</code> sessions, Araxys automatically revokes the <strong>oldest</strong>
    session to make room for the new one. This prevents users from sharing credentials across too many devices while
    ensuring the most recent session is always valid. The enforcement happens at session creation time — when a new
    session is created after login, the limit is checked and the oldest session is revoked if necessary.
  </p>

  <h3 id="revocation">Manual Revocation</h3>
  <p>
    The <code>revoke_session()</code> method allows immediate invalidation of a specific session by ID. This is useful
    for:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>"Log out all devices" features</li>
    <li>Admin panel session management</li>
    <li>Security responses to compromised sessions</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Revoked sessions are marked as invalid in storage and any subsequent request using that session is rejected.
  </p>

  <h3 id="cleanup-loop">Background Cleanup Loop</h3>
  <p>
    A background <code>asyncio</code> task runs every <code>cleanup_interval</code> seconds and purges sessions that
    have exceeded their <code>session_ttl</code>. This prevents the session store from accumulating stale entries.
    The loop can be gracefully terminated by calling <code>shield.shutdown()</code> during application shutdown.
  </p>

  <h2 id="configuration">Configuration</h2>
  <p>Configure session management via the <code>SessionConfig</code> model:</p>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code><span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys <span class="token-keyword">import</span> AraxysConfig, AraxysShield
<span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys.core.config <span class="token-keyword">import</span> SessionConfig

shield = <span class="token-function">AraxysShield</span>(
    app,
    <span class="token-function">AraxysConfig</span>(
        <span class="token-param">secret_key</span>=<span class="token-string">"your-32-char-secret-key-here!!!!"</span>,
        <span class="token-param">session</span>=<span class="token-function">SessionConfig</span>(
            <span class="token-param">enabled</span>=<span class="token-bool">True</span>,
            <span class="token-param">max_concurrent</span>=<span class="token-number">3</span>,
            <span class="token-param">session_ttl</span>=<span class="token-number">86400</span>,
            <span class="token-param">cleanup_interval</span>=<span class="token-number">300</span>,
        ),
    ),
)</code></pre>
  </div>

  <h3 id="config-reference">Configuration Reference</h3>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Field</th>
        <th>Type</th>
        <th>Default</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>enabled</code></td><td><code>bool</code></td><td><code>True</code></td><td>Enable session management</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>max_concurrent</code></td><td><code>int</code></td><td><code>5</code></td><td>Max concurrent sessions per user</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>session_ttl</code></td><td><code>int</code></td><td><code>86400</code></td><td>Session TTL in seconds (24h)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>cleanup_interval</code></td><td><code>int</code></td><td><code>300</code></td><td>Cleanup interval in seconds</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <div class="alert alert--info">
    <div class="alert-title">
      <span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="font-size: 16px;">info</span>
      Cleanup Loop
    </div>
    <div class="alert-content">
      The cleanup loop runs as a background <code>asyncio</code> task. Use <code>shield.shutdown()</code> to gracefully terminate it during application shutdown, ensuring no in-progress cleanup operations are interrupted.
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="code-examples">Code Examples</h2>

  <h3>Session Creation After Login</h3>
  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code><span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys <span class="token-keyword">import</span> AraxysShield

shield = <span class="token-function">AraxysShield</span>(app, config)
session_manager = shield.session_manager

<span class="token-comment"># After successful login</span>
session = <span class="token-keyword">await</span> session_manager.<span class="token-function">create_session</span>(
    user_id=<span class="token-string">"user_abc123"</span>,
    metadata=&#123;<span class="token-string">"ip"</span>: request.client.host, <span class="token-string">"user_agent"</span>: <span class="token-string">"Mozilla/5.0 ..."</span>&#125;,
)
<span class="token-comment"># The oldest session is auto-revoked if max_concurrent is exceeded</span>
<span class="token-builtin">print</span>(<span class="token-string">f"Session created: </span>&#123;session.id&#125;<span class="token-string">"</span>)</code></pre>
  </div>

  <h3>Revoking a Session</h3>
  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code><span class="token-comment"># Manual session revocation</span>
<span class="token-keyword">await</span> session_manager.<span class="token-function">revoke_session</span>(<span class="token-string">"session_xyz789"</span>)
<span class="token-comment"># Audit event emitted automatically</span>

<span class="token-comment"># Revoke all sessions for a user ("log out all devices")</span>
sessions = <span class="token-keyword">await</span> session_manager.<span class="token-function">get_user_sessions</span>(<span class="token-string">"user_abc123"</span>)
<span class="token-keyword">for</span> s <span class="token-keyword">in</span> sessions:
    <span class="token-keyword">await</span> session_manager.<span class="token-function">revoke_session</span>(s.id)</code></pre>
  </div>

  <h3>Checking Active Sessions</h3>
  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code><span class="token-comment"># List all active sessions for a user</span>
active_sessions = <span class="token-keyword">await</span> session_manager.<span class="token-function">get_user_sessions</span>(
    <span class="token-param">user_id</span>=<span class="token-string">"user_abc123"</span>,
    <span class="token-param">include_expired</span>=<span class="token-bool">False</span>,
)
<span class="token-builtin">print</span>(<span class="token-string">f"Active sessions: </span>&#123;len(active_sessions)&#125;<span class="token-string">"</span>)
<span class="token-keyword">for</span> session <span class="token-keyword">in</span> active_sessions:
    <span class="token-builtin">print</span>(<span class="token-string">f"  - </span>&#123;session.id&#125;<span class="token-string"> (created: </span>&#123;session.created_at&#125;<span class="token-string">)"</span>)</code></pre>
  </div>

  <h2 id="integration">Integration</h2>
  <p>
    Session management ties into <strong>JWT authentication</strong> and <strong>CSRF protection</strong>. When a
    JWT token is issued, Araxys creates a corresponding session. The session ID can be embedded in the JWT claims
    for server-side validation.
  </p>
  <p>
    Session storage uses the same backend pattern as other Araxys modules — <code>InMemoryBackend</code> for
    single-process deployments and <code>RedisBackend</code> for multi-worker setups. When a session is revoked,
    an audit event is emitted so your logging system can record the action.
  </p>

</DocsLayout>
